"To give a name to the fallen is a moral duty, before scientific - they explain from the association House of Resistance -. Article 6 of the Civil Code and the Geneva Conventions on Human Rights state that the right to name must be guaranteed to all, even to the dead, as a distinctive sign of the individuality of a person."
Eighty years after the Nazi massacres of 1944, the Labanof and the House of Resistance will attempt to guarantee this right by rebuilding one of the most tragic pages of the Partisan Resistance. During 2023, laboratory technicians analysed the remains of the 33 unknown partisans to reconstruct their biological profile. Now the hope is that, with the collaboration of the relatives of the missing partisans and through the examination of the Dna or photographic recontrials, you can return a name to the unknown buried in the shrine of Fondotoce.&nbsp;

