On the site of the clashes and along the escape routes were seized helmets, used for possible beams, bats, sticks, screwdrivers and a large knife that is used to cut the sushi. Two later Romanessts who had been reported for lacero-contuse wounds in a capital hospital were conducted in the offices of Digos. Claudio Corbolotti, the head of the irreducibles of Lazio, was arrested for aggravated rissa and port of arms during sporting events because it would be found in possession of a stick. He had already been sentenced to a year for the blitz of 24 April 2019 in which some tens of latial ultras near Piazzale Loreto, in Milan, exhibited a banner in "honour at Benito Mussolini". He was also arrested for a 41-year-old Romanesque. They have added a latial fan arrested in the Olympic for official public resistance and are denounced for possession of smoking at the stadium. "It's been a long time since we launched the alarm that in and around the stadiums the episodes of violence are increasing exponentially," denounced the Secretary General of the Police Union Sap, Stefano Paoloni, "the one of today is the umpteenth demonstration that even the level of danger of the clashes continues to grow". "We need rapid interventions and no tolerance for those who use violence," said Paoloni, "and the support of football companies is fundamental to condemn these episodes. Also for this reason, in recent months, we launched an appeal to establish a Day against violence in the stadiums in memory of Inspector Filippo Raciti". &nbsp;
