AGI -&nbsp; There are already 29 suicides of prisoners in Italian prisons since the beginning of the year. A number that disturbs the risk of recording at the end of 2024 another sad record equaling or exceeding the 84 suicides of 2022, annus horribilis with an average suicide every 4 days. According to Antigone's data, the previous negative record was in 2009, when in total the suicides of prisoners in prison were 72 on a population of over 61,000 prisoners. The Minister of Justice, Carlo Nordio, only two days ago intervened by signing a decree with which he immediately allocates 5 million euros to prevent suicides and reduce the psychological discomfort of the prison population. The last suicide in prison is the one recorded in the penitentiary institute of Cagliari on April 2, where a 32-year-old took his life by hanging in his cell. Alarm also for the suicides of the prison police officers, 3 have been killed since the beginning of the year. "The rhythm of the dead in these first months of the year is impressive - it has emphasized to the AGI&nbsp; the president of the association Antigone, Patrizio Gonnella - surely the intervention of the government goes in the direction of greater availability of human resources, in this case of psychologists and this is good. As well as the increase in pay for the same psychologists working in prisons. It's not enough, though, because you need to invest in the quality of life. Half the suicides take place in the first six months of detention, which means that we must intervene at that time, not only with psychologists and staff support, but avoiding that they end up in the worst cells in the prison. Increasing phone calls with family members and more generally filling the prison for most of the hours inmates spend in jail and this is devastating from the psycho-physical point of view. It is necessary to modernize and make life less medieval." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"We hope this year not to exceed the numbers of 2022, the suicide of a prisoner is always a defeat for the state - said to the AGI&nbsp; the general secretary of the Sappe, the autonomous union of the penitentiary police, Donato Capece - the causes are always to be traced to overcrowding and the shortage of staff. Suicides unfortunately, despite all our effort, you cannot prevent them. In Teramo in March, for example, a young detainee of 20 years had a dialogue with an agent until 4:00 in the morning and it seemed that there were no problems, then at 5:30 was found hanged." In 2021 the number of suicides in prison, according to data published by the Dap, the Department of Penitentiary Administration, was 57. In 2020 61 people took their lives away from the Italian prisons; in 2019 were 53; in 2018 were 67; in 2017 suicides were 52; in 2016 were 39; 39 cases also in 2015; in 2014 were recorded 43; in 2013 there were 42 suicides; in 2012 were 56; in 2011 there were 63 suicides; in 2010 there were 55 suicides. Going back in time other record years were 2001 with 69 suicides and 1993 with 61 prisoners who took their lives. "Apulia is the region with the most crowded prisons of detainees, 160% in front of the 120% national - it has explained to the AGI&nbsp;Federico Pilagatti, the secretary of Sappe Puglia - suffers more of this situation also because of the serious shortage of staff that is 20% according to the supplied in 2023. Last year the 'black eye' with 5 suicides registered in the prison of Taranto. In the penitentiary of Taranto, 280 agents for 950 prisoners work." &nbsp;
